{{Top|legends=Plasticene Thermite Cube}}
'''Plasticene thermite''' was a type of substance that could be shipped and was considered to be contraband during the [[Imperial Era]]. It shared its name<ref name="Outlaws">''[[Star Wars Outlaws]]''</ref> with [[Plasticene]], a substance used in [[starship]]s,<ref name="TFA">[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens (novelization)|''Star Wars: The Force Awakens'' novelization]]</ref> and [[thermite]], a substance used to make the shell casing.<ref name="Swoop">{{IDWAdventuresCite-2017|issue=21|story=Swoop Racers}}</ref>

{{Gamemechanics|Star Wars Outlaws|canon=1}}
In [[3 ABY]],<ref name="OutlawsDate">{{OutlawsDate}}</ref> the [[scoundrel]] [[Kay Vess]] accepted an underworld contract for the [[Pyke Syndicate]] to [[Smuggler|smuggle]] a shipment of plasticene thermite from [[Myrra Spaceport]] on the [[jungle]] [[planet]] [[Akiva]] to the Pyke's [[Pyke Crystal Mine|crystal mine]] in the [[Stormhollow]] region of Akiva.<ref name="Outlaws" />
{{Endgame}}

==Behind the scenes==
Plasticene thermite was mentioned in the current ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] continuity as part of the optional contract "Deliver Pyke contraband" for the [[2024]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Outlaws]]'', which was developed by [[Massive Entertainment]] and published by [[Ubisoft]].<ref name="Outlaws" /> 

[[Plasticene Thermite Cube|Plasticene thermite gel]] was originally introduced in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity; first being mentioned in ''[[Galaxy Guide 11: Criminal Organizations]]'' a supplimentry book for the ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]''.  Galaxy Guide 11 was written by [[Rick D. Stuart]] and published by [[West End Games]] in 1994.<ref name="Galaxy Guide 11">''[[Galaxy Guide 11: Criminal Organizations]]''</ref>

